<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Wooltru shr up slightly, wary on prospects.</title>
<headline>Wooltru shr up slightly, wary on prospects.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Yr ended June 30</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, attrib (cts)     109.1	 vs 100.3</p>
<p>    Div (cts)    24 making 42	   vs 38</p>
<p>    Net profit		398.3	 vs 357.7</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   573.2	 vs 542.6</p>
<p>    Tax			 183.5	 vs 179.2</p>
<p>    Exceptional items     51.2	  vs 36.0</p>
<p>    Revenue		 9,711.3	 vs 8,152.0</p>
<p>Div payable October 17</p>
<p>on register September 6</p>
<p>Full name: Wooltru Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - The group said it expected difficult trading conditions in the current year as the economy moved sideways, or even backwards, from a consumer's point of view. But it said there should be a pleasing profit from Asutralia.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
